cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper discusses the challenges of distilling useful principles from a large body of research literature in machine learning, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. However, the focus on methodologies and applications in computer vision, natural language processing, and reinforcement learning suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely categories. Additionally, the mention of computer vision specifically suggests cs.CV (Computer Vision) as a possible category. The mention of natural language processing suggests cs.CL (Computation and Language) as another possible category. Finally, the mention of reinforcement learning suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as a possible category.
